result.execSummary:
The defendant Omar Villalobos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Methamphetamine (>50g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(e)4.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: BOND APPLIED - fine pd in full.
May not possess any weapons, including firearms.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.
*  Pay supervision fees.
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not be in taverns or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants or grocery stores.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment.  Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program.
*  Pay fine of $24,000.00 and court costs including all applicable surcharges.
*  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.
*  DE is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay DNA surcharge and notice is given.
*  Pay costs of legal representation or Advocate Counsel fees for the defense of the case, to be determined within 60 days.
Spend 1yr in the county jail, commencing forthwith.  Huber privileges are allowed.  Cooperate with the Child Support Agency to establish paternity and/or to pay child support and make all court appearances in any paternity action.  May not have contact with Jesus Flores, unless otherwise permitted by the court.  May not possess any weapons, including firearms.

Attorney Thomas Binger appeared for the State. Defendant, Omar  Villalobos, appeared with Attorney Patrick Kiernan Cafferty. Interpreter Leo Martin in Court.  Clerk: PT
Interpreter Martin is sworn in.  Case is resolved.  DE pleads Guilty; found guilty by the court.  PSI is waived by parties and sentencing arguments are made.  Sentence is withheld and DE is placed on probation for 5 years with conditions.  As a condition court imposes 1 year in the KCJ forthwith and DE is taken into custody.  Huber & Work Crew privileges are authorized.   Court imposes a fine of $24,000 plus costs and surcharges.  Cash Bond on deposit shall be applied.  Atty Cafferty will be drafting a bond assignment for the court to review and approve for any bond balance that remains.  No contact with J. Flores unless permitted by the court only.  Appeal Rights, Firearm Warning & Voting Acknowledgement given.
